{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/3-text-distances-that-every-data-scientist-should-know-7fcdf850e510", "time": 1683002995.270036, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/3-text-distances-that-every-data-scientist-should-know-7fcdf850e510/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "3 text distances that every data scientist should know | by Joos Korstanje | Towards Data Science", "h1": "3 text distances that every data scientist should know", "description": "In a previous article, I described three distances that every data scientist should know. Those distances where geometric distances: from a point to a point. In this article, I talk about distance\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/3-distances-that-every-data-scientist-should-know-59d864e5030a", "anchor_text": "three distances that every data scientist should know", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_vector", "anchor_text": "For looking up some mathematics check out here if needed", "paragraph_index": 15}, {"url": "https://scikit-learn.org/stable/modules/generated/sklearn.metrics.pairwise.cosine_similarity.html", "anchor_text": "the scikit learn library in Python", "paragraph_index": 16}], "all_paragraphs": ["In a previous article, I described three distances that every data scientist should know. Those distances where geometric distances: from a point to a point. In this article, I talk about distance measures from one text to another text.", "Measuring the distance from one text to another works differently than from a point another.", "The Hamming Distance compares every letter of the two strings based on position. So the first letter of word 1 is compared to the first letter of word 2 etc etc.", "The Hamming Distance compares every letter of the two strings based purely on position.", "An advantage of the Hamming Distance is that it is very fast and simple to do this position-wise comparison. On the other hand, critics are that it cannot take into account two strings with an unequal number of letters. Another critic is that it is too strict, for example, \u201cabcdefg\u201d and \u201cbcdefgh\u201d are considered totally different, while 6 out of 7 characters are the same.", "The Levenshtein Distance is the number of operations needed to convert one string into another. So every edit needed will add 1 to the Levenshtein Distance.", "The Levenshtein Distance is the number of operations needed to convert one string into another.", "Levenshtein distance is much more intuitive. Where Hamming Distance indicated that \u2018abcdefg\u2019 and \u2018bcdefgh\u2019 are totally different, in Levenshtein Distance they are relatively similar.", "On the other hand, Levenshtein Distance does take more time to compute and the algorithm is less simple.", "The Cosine Distance is rather different from the previously discussed metrics, in that it considers the distance between two documents. It is commonly used in Natural Language Processing.", "The Cosine Distance applies to the vector representation of documents.", "Central to the Cosine Distance, or the more often used Cosine Similarity, is the idea of vectorizing your text: converting a text into numerical data. The easiest approach is to use a word count vectorizer:", "Step 1: Get all the unique words of your combined text documents", "Step 2: Make a vector for each document by doing a word count", "Step 3: Compute the similarity between vectors using Cosine Similarity (similarity is the opposite of distance)", "The formula for similarity is computed by computing the dot product of your two vectors divided by the norm of a times the norm of b. For looking up some mathematics check out here if needed.", "To compute this, we can use the scikit learn library in Python. For the current example, it gives the following result:", "So 1 and 2 are most similar, then 2 and 3 are most similar and 1 and 3 are most different, exactly as expected.", "In this article, I have shared 3 ways to compute distances on text data, from very basic to relatively complex.", "I hope it\u2019s been informative for you and I wish you good luck with your journey to data science! Stay tuned for more ;)", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Data Scientist \u2014 Machine Learning \u2014 R, Python, AWS, SQL"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F7fcdf850e510&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2F3-text-distances-that-every-data-scientist-should-know-7fcdf850e510&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2F3-text-distances-that-every-data-scientist-should-know-7fcdf850e510&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2F3-text-distances-that-every-data-scientist-should-know-7fcdf850e510&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation